<h3>Category: Files</h3>

<p>
With the object type "files" and its version control, i-doit administeres all uploaded files.
Therefore all uploads taking place in this object. Inside it there are the categories "Current file", 
"File versions" and an overview of the currently assigned objects visible. These points are located
under the directory "files" in the left menutree of the new file object.
</p>

<p>
A new file is created as follows: <br/>
<ul style="list-style:square;">
	<li>Add a new entry to "File versions" and upload the file with your browser there.</li>
	<li>At this point of time, the new Fileupload is automatically the current File version</li>
	<li>Afterwards you can still change the current version by selecting "Current file" in the menutree and changing the version there</li>
</ul>
<br />
</p>

<p>
<strong>File assignment:</strong>
<br />
An uploaded file can be assigned to another object (like server or application for example) within the categories "files" and "handbook" 
in their respective object.
</p>